<h1 class="text-center page-header">About us</h1>

<div class="container p-3 primary-color-200"
    style="border: 1px solid black; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 4px 3px 5px 1px;">
    <p class="indent">
        Sustainable Oceans and Reefs, is a pioneering organization dedicated to advancing marine conservation through
        innovative approaches. Focused on the development of in situ rearing mariculture systems, SOAR aims to harness
        the potential of sea urchins for restorative purposes. By carefully cultivating urchins in their natural
        habitats, SOAR seeks to contribute to the enhancement of marine ecosystems, particularly coral reefs, through
        the ecologically sound deployment of these sea creatures.
    </p>
    <p class="indent">
        In addition to its mariculture initiatives, SOAR plays a vital role in supporting reef restoration research and
        practitioners through its contracting and consulting services. The organization collaborates with a diverse
        range of stakeholders, including scientists, environmentalists, and local communities, to facilitate
        comprehensive reef restoration projects. Through its multifaceted approach, SOAR is at the forefront of
        fostering environmental resilience and promoting the sustainable management of marine resources.
    </p>
</div>
